{"kind":"textbox","id":"sh/032lszqt","slide":12,"name":"text","text":"- Stemming and lemmatization are usually not applied before BPE-style LLM tokenization\n- They can destroy reversibility and remove information the model may need\n- They remain relevant for search, retrieval, feature engineering, and analysis","textPreview":"- Stemming and lemmatization are usually not applied before BPE-style LLM tokenization | - They can destroy reversibility and remove info...","textChars":241,"textLines":3,"bbox":[74,274,488,240]}
